featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
Punjab is historically and culturally connected with Indo-Iranian (Aryan) heritage. Already this region has been the gateway to the Indian subcontinent for western invaders. As a result of these attacks, many caste-communities, religions and cultural heritages were born here. One of the earliest cultures of South Asia in prehistoric times was the Harappan culture in Punjab.

The people living here speak an Indo-Aryan dialect, which is called Punjabi. Greeks, Arabs, Turks, Mughals, Afghans, Baluchis and British also lived here.

featured_reviews.review_id:
This masjid is called big "bari" masjid.
I think this masjid was founded in 1890.when our forefathers inhabit this village.
There is also a seminary for female muslim students to learn holy quran.
There is also shrine of grand father of my father , " mian ge ameer ahmed ra and haji shareef zaildar.
Mian g ameer ahmed was very pious man and spiritual desciple of mian sher muhammad ra of sharqpur shareef.
He was died in masjid.therefore also burried in masjid.
